  <header>
    <h1>🌿 Supporting Carers with Dignity and Insight</h1>
    <p>A tribute and resource hub for Australia’s 3 million+ unpaid carers</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>💛 Who Are Unpaid Carers?</h2>
    <p>Unpaid carers are family, friends or neighbours offering support without formal compensation. They assist with daily tasks, provide emotional care, and navigate complex systems — often while working or parenting themselves.</p>
    <blockquote>“Caring is not a one-size-fits-all experience.” — National Carer Strategy 2024–2034</blockquote>
    <p>Explore <a href="https://www.carergateway.gov.au" target="_blank">Carer Gateway</a> for free support services.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>👩‍👧 Resources for Working Mums</h2>
    <ul class="resource-links">
      <li><a href="https://workingmumma.com.au">Working Mumma</a> – Confidence-building & return-to-work tips</li>
      <li><a href="https://www.workathomemums.com.au">Work At Home Mums</a> – Flexible job ideas & support</li>
      <li><a href="https://www.gidgetfoundation.org.au/fact-sheets/emotional-wellbeing-in-the-workplace-for-mums">Gidget Foundation</a> – Mental wellbeing tools</li>
      <li><a href="http://www.careermatters.com.au/resources-for-mums.html">Career Matters</a> – Grants, childcare & career advice</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>📚 Evidence-Based Insights</h2>
    <table class="needs-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Domain</th>
          <th>Key Needs</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Physical Wellbeing</td>
          <td>Respite care, sleep support, health checks</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Mental Health</td>
          <td>Counselling, peer support, trauma-informed design</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Financial Security</td>
          <td>Income support, flexible work, recognition</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Social Inclusion</td>
          <td>Community connection, cultural safety</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Education & Advocacy</td>
          <td>Training access, carer literacy, reform</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>See <a href="https://documents.uow.edu.au/content/groups/public/@web/@chsd/documents/doc/uow178839.pdf" target="_blank">Effective Caring Report – UOW</a> for international evidence synthesis.</p>
  </section>

